Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.320
You have four 4s: 4 ,4 ,4 and 4,

00:00:03.800 --> 00:00:07.880
and using all four 4s

00:00:08.380 --> 00:00:11.900
you have to create, using the mathematical operators,

00:00:11.900 --> 00:00:14.140
as many numbers as you can.

00:00:14.500 --> 00:00:16.640
So, the way that we start this normally, if we're

00:00:16.650 --> 00:00:19.520
doing "level 1" four 4s, will be,

00:00:19.520 --> 00:00:22.800
all that you're allowed to use is, addition, subtraction,

00:00:22.800 --> 00:00:24.200
multiplication and division.

00:00:24.540 --> 00:00:28.000
Let's start at 0, and we gonna then go to 1, then go to 2.

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:31.520
So, with 0, how do you get four 4s to equal 0?

00:00:31.520 --> 00:00:32.800
It is kind of easy.

00:00:32.800 --> 00:00:37.980
You can go 4 minus 4 plus 4 minus 4. That's 0.

00:00:37.980 --> 00:00:40.000
Brilliant! We've got 0.

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:42.520
Okay, let's put the four 4s again to equal 1.

00:00:42.520 --> 00:00:47.120
Well, we could do 4 divided by 4, now that's 1,

00:00:47.120 --> 00:00:50.620
plus 4 minus 4, or we could have done

00:00:50.620 --> 00:00:56.900
4 divided by 4, divided by 4 divided by 4 which is 1 divided by 1, which is 1.

00:00:56.900 --> 00:00:59.280
Again that's 1. There are lots of different ways,

00:00:59.300 --> 00:01:00.840
and they get a little bit more complicated.

00:01:00.840 --> 00:01:03.180
And we can go and do 2. And we can

00:01:03.180 --> 00:01:05.700
carry on upwards.

00:01:06.940 --> 00:01:10.740
How far? Ten? A hundred? A thousand?

00:01:10.740 --> 00:01:12.300
I'm going to show you today,

00:01:12.460 --> 00:01:14.060
Brady, your mind will be blown!

00:01:14.180 --> 00:01:17.260
I will prove the four 4s all the way up to

00:01:17.260 --> 00:01:18.540
infinity.

00:01:19.280 --> 00:01:20.800
[Brady]: You can make every number?

00:01:20.800 --> 00:01:23.480
You can make EVERY number up to infinity.

00:01:23.500 --> 00:01:25.880
It's a fantastic little proof and we're

00:01:25.880 --> 00:01:27.520
going to get there. We need to actually be,

00:01:27.520 --> 00:01:29.700
we need to clarify the operators first.

00:01:29.700 --> 00:01:32.600
We can get up to 10 just with these:

00:01:32.700 --> 00:01:35.660
plus, minus, multiplication and division.

00:01:35.800 --> 00:01:39.200
To get up to 20, we need to introduce

00:01:39.200 --> 00:01:41.200
some other things: what we need to

00:01:41.200 --> 00:01:44.620
introduce is concatenation,

00:01:44.860 --> 00:01:49.180
which means that just that we've got 4 4 4 4, we can

00:01:49.180 --> 00:01:51.140
bring them together, so we can actually

00:01:51.200 --> 00:01:54.060
bring them together and consider that, say forty-four.

00:01:54.060 --> 00:02:03.100
We introduce the decimal point so one of these could be zero point four.

00:02:03.360 --> 00:02:09.240
And we introduce the factorial, which means it's 4 times 3 times 2 times 1.

00:02:09.580 --> 00:02:12.940
And also, we need the square root,

00:02:13.040 --> 00:02:14.940
so square root of 4 is obviously 2.

00:02:14.940 --> 00:02:17.680
You might think, well, that's spoiling this other

00:02:17.680 --> 00:02:20.300
little beautiful simple puzzle, but

00:02:20.300 --> 00:02:21.860
actually factorial, concatenation,

00:02:21.880 --> 00:02:24.340
decimal, and square root are really basic.

00:02:24.340 --> 00:02:26.360
They're kind of in our basic armory.

00:02:26.360 --> 00:02:28.640
so I think that's fine. Well, how far can we do

00:02:28.640 --> 00:02:30.800
with all of these? We can definitely get

00:02:30.800 --> 00:02:33.880
up all the way to 50. Higher than 50?

00:02:33.880 --> 00:02:36.200
We can get up pretty high, we can get up to 100,

00:02:36.200 --> 00:02:40.500
but in fact we need to start introducing other ones, and

00:02:40.540 --> 00:02:42.800
I'll show you-- one of the ones that doesn't work

00:02:42.800 --> 00:02:44.120
with all these, is, say, 99.

00:02:44.120 --> 00:02:46.100
I'm gonna show you how to do 99.

00:02:46.100 --> 00:02:49.880
So 99, there are different ways to do this, but this

00:02:49.880 --> 00:02:51.640
is the one that I quite like. It all depends

00:02:51.640 --> 00:02:53.860
which is the new symbol you're going to do.

00:02:53.860 --> 00:03:00.580
4 over 4, as a percentage is 100

00:03:00.580 --> 00:03:03.320
minus 1 is 99.

00:03:03.320 --> 00:03:05.380
So that's quite a clever way

00:03:05.380 --> 00:03:08.040
and the good fun thing about the four 4s

00:03:08.040 --> 00:03:09.680
well, just say you're bored on a

00:03:09.680 --> 00:03:12.120
plane or a train, you can just start at

00:03:12.120 --> 00:03:14.040
the beginning and then just go up and

00:03:14.040 --> 00:03:15.680
